Title: Full Stack Engineer Lead (Java / C# / .NET)
Job_Description:
IT Quality Control Senior Advisor (SDET)
Software Development Engineer in Test(SDET) - Quality Control Senior Advisor - AIM
The Software Development Engineer in Test (SDET) position plays a key role in the development of AIM's platform. SDET at AIM Specialty Health is a developer with the primary responsibility of writing automation frameworks and tools to test products. It combines the "building" aspect of software design engineering with the "breaking" aspect of software test engineering. This role involves writing code that automatically verifies the quality of the product. SDETs at AIM Specialty Health can understand software internals, debug code, automate repetitive tasks, and implement new tools and frameworks needed to streamline our quality process. Our SDETs work directly with both Software Development Engineers and Quality Assurance Engineers to understand project features, review technical designs, and implement automated test tools that help deliver quality features with efficiency. Our SDETs understand customer usage models and can develop test plans and test cases that approximate real-world environments and scenarios.

Title: IT Manager (Application Development)
Job_Description:
The Senior Manager – Delivery Manager is responsible for providing leadership and support for both the Care and the Digital teams within the Elevance Division. This resource supports all Lines of Business (Commercial, Medicare, Medicaid, and affiliated clients). This person is accountable for supporting the teams in the CVS Health Care and Digital to achieve goals and objectives, to provide superior service to members, and to develop positive relationships with client resources. Specifically, this leader will ensure that the client and the PBM enterprise goals are aligned, and that planning and execution to achieve those goals are thorough and that status is communicated effectively. This role will partner with the Elevance Division Operations and Account Management organization, the Member Operations organization, the Digital and IT organizations, other internal partners within CVS Caremark, and key operational leaders to provide superior client support. They will monitor execution on priorities and serve as an escalation path to assist with removal of barriers. Finally, they will engage in highly escalated member issues to ensure consistent, data-driven communications and sustainable resolution.

You will work in a dynamic, high pressure environment where teamwork and personal drive will be essential to your success. As a key resource in operations and delivery, you will demonstrate your strong problem definition and project management skills while remaining compliant to internal and external rules, policies, and regulations. You will also need to use your strong client facing and relationship development skills, including developing and presenting presentation to accomplish your goals. The contributions you make will ensure CVS Health maintains its position as a leader in the healthcare marketplace.
A successful candidate in this role will influence a cross functional team in a large matrix organization. This candidate will need to quickly build relationships with key stakeholders to identify and leverage operational efficiencies to bring to the division. In additional to leveraging internal stakeholders, this candidate will need to build relationships with their client contact to understand needs and deliver results. Additionally, your role will entail:

Minimum: 75,400
Maximum: 158,300

Please keep in mind that this range represents the pay range for all positions in the job grade within which this position falls. The actual salary offer will take into account a wide range of factors, including location.
